name: Let's Fall In Love
comments: Her piano  is  lovely  too, lots  of Oscar Peterson and Count Basie  influences
diana cold...???  haha...somebody's emotion meter must be broken...i mean sure subjectivity and all that...but...by the numbers???...lol...

Well , alyoucha, all of us have individual tastes and make subjective choices re likes and dislikes. One does not have to like DK, or any other singer. And if she comes up on your MG Radio, well just ban the song each time. :)

Someone has to say it... ok maybe I'm the only one who feels that way. I find Diana Krall totally emotionless, cold and bland. Singing by numbers. I'm annoyed that she keeps coming up on my "Melody Gardot radio". Melody... mmm.. now that's a woman that stirs emotions.
Nice, but nothing beats Sinatra's version! (sorry Diana, you know I love you!)
Aww, Dianah... This was a bit unexpected...
diana's piano and vocal...sweet as usual...john clayton on bass...
one of my favs from her paris live album...this really swings...the music accompany is great...and diana's piano and voice are right on the mark...
Nat King Cole -  Let's Fall in Love
